{{nihongo|'''Junya Itō'''|伊東 純也|Itō Jun'ya|born 9 March 1993}} is a Japanese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)#Winger|winger]] or a [[Forward (association football)#Inside forward|forward]] for [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[KRC Genk|Genk]] and the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]].

==Club career==
===Early club career===
After attending [[Kanagawa University]] for four years,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jsports.co.jp/press/article/N2015071015441302.html|script-title=ja:「ガンバは強いっていうイメージはありますけど、やれないことはないと思います」ガンバ大阪 × ヴァンフォーレ甲府|access-date=30 May 2016|language=ja|archive-date=28 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028151737/https://www.jsports.co.jp/press/article/N2015071015441302.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> Itō first became a Special Designated Player for [[Ventforet Kofu]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ventforet.jp/news/press_release/507572|script-title=ja:神奈川大学 伊東純也選手 来季新加入内定のお知らせ|website=Ventforet Kofu|language=ja|access-date=30 May 2016|archive-date=12 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312141053/http://www.ventforet.jp/news/press_release/507572|url-status=live}}</ref> and obtained a new contract with the [[J1 League]] side.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20160502/437404.html|script-title=ja:手倉森ジャパンの切り札となるか...「やたらと速い」柏の"IJ"こと伊東純也とは|website=Soccer King|publisher=FromOne co., Ltd|language=ja|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160604191639/http://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20160502/437404.html|archive-date=4 June 2016}}</ref> His first professional season attracted attention from Chiba-based [[Kashiwa Reysol]], which signed him in January 2016.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ja:伊東　純也選手が移籍加入|url=http://blog.reysol.co.jp/news/2016/014215.html|website=Kashiwa Reysol Official Site|access-date=30 May 2016|language=ja|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160109112325/http://blog.reysol.co.jp/news/2016/014215.html|archive-date=9 January 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 31 January 2019, Itō moved from Kashiwa Reysol to [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]] on a one-year loan.<ref>{{cite web |title=Football: Japan winger Junya Ito reveals title ambitions with Genk |url=https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2019/02/3d865316440d-soccer-japan-winger-ito-reveals-title-ambitions-with-genk.html |website=Kyodo News|date=12 February 2019 |access-date=4 March 2019 |archive-date=12 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312141120/https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2019/02/3d865316440d-soccer-japan-winger-ito-reveals-title-ambitions-with-genk.html |url-status=live }}</ref> On 18 September, he made his Champions League debut as a starter in the group stage match against [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]]. On 30 March 2020, Itō signed permanently with Genk on a three-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=30 March 2020 |title=Japanner Ito blijft definitief bij Genk: "Hij is een publiekslieveling" |url=https://sporza.be/nl/2020/03/30/japanner-ito-blijft-langer-bij-racing-genk/ |access-date=29 July 2022 |website=sporza.be|language=nl |archive-date=20 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220920170549/https://sporza.be/nl/2020/03/30/japanner-ito-blijft-langer-bij-racing-genk/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Stade Reims and return to Genk===
On 29 July 2022, Itō joined [[Ligue 1]] club [[Stade de Reims|Reims]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Junya Ito onderweg naar Stade Reims|url=https://www.krcgenk.be/nl/nieuws/4764/junya-ito-onderweg-naar-stade-reims |access-date=29 July 2022|website=KRC Genk|publisher=Sanmax Projects|language=nl |archive-date=12 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220812025516/https://www.krcgenk.be/nl/nieuws/4764/junya-ito-onderweg-naar-stade-reims |url-status=live }}</ref> On 23 October, he scored the winner in a 2–1 victory against [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=23 October 2022 |title=Reims vs. Auxerre 2–1 |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2022/10/23/france/ligue-1/stade-de-reims/association-de-la-jeunesse-auxerroise/3802258/|website=Soccerway|publisher=Platform Group|access-date=19 December 2023}}</ref> In the [[2023–24 Ligue 1]] opening game on 12 August 2023, Itō scored a stunning opening goal against [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]], but Reims eventually lost 2–1.{{Citation needed|date=January 2025}} In August 2025, following his club's relegation from Ligue 1 in the [[2024–25 Ligue 1|2024–25 season]], Itō returned to Genk and signed a three-year contract.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Football: Japan winger Ito rejoins Genk from relegated Reims|url=https://mainichi.jp/english/articles/20250810/p2g/00m/0sp/037000c|newspaper=[[Mainichi Shimbun]]|date=10 August 2025|access-date=5 September 2025}}</ref>

== International career ==
Itō made his [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]] debut{{Clarification needed|reason=Against which country? In what tournament?|date=January 2025}} in 2017.{{Citation needed|date=January 2025}} He was selected for [[Hajime Moriyasu]]'s [[2022 FIFA World Cup squads|final World Cup squad]] in October 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Moriyasu names Japan squad for Qatar 2022|url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/japan-squad-announced-for-world-cup-qatar-2022|website=FIFA|date=1 November 2022}}</ref>

== Controversy ==
=== Adultery and sexual assault allegations ===
On 31 January 2024, ''[[Shukan Shincho]]'' reported that police had launched an investigation into Itō following a criminal complaint filed by two women alleging that he had engaged in [[sexual misconduct]] with them while they were intoxicated at a hotel in [[Osaka]] without their consent after a match for Japan against [[Peru national football team|Peru]] in June 2023.<ref>{{Cite news |date=31 January 2024 |title=Football: Japan player Junya Ito probed over sexual assault allegation |work=Kyodo News |url=https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2024/02/0cb359a0ec78-football-japan-player-ito-probed-over-sexual-assault-allegation.html}}</ref>

In response to this report, the [[Japan Football Association]] decided on February 1 to withdraw Ito from the ongoing [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]] after considering Ito's physical and mental condition.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/202402010001257.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240201120045/https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/202402010001257.html|script-title=ja:伊東純也、虚偽告訴容疑の告訴状を大阪府警に提出 女性２人への性加害報道を受けて|language=ja|website=[[Nikkan Sports]]|date=1 February 2024|archive-date=1 February 2024|access-date=1 February 2024}}</ref>

On 1 February, Itō filed a criminal complaint against the two women with the Osaka Prefectural Police for filing false complaints. On 19 February, he filed a lawsuit against the two women at the Osaka District Court, claiming that their sponsorship contracts were terminated due to false complaints and demanding 200 million yen in damages.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.yahoo.co.jp/articles/264f6146d52071abf72f35c3faaa467cf45bc0f2|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240219050720/https://news.yahoo.co.jp/articles/264f6146d52071abf72f35c3faaa467cf45bc0f2|script-title=ja:【速報】伊東純也選手が性被害訴える女性側に「２億円」の損害賠償求め民事で提訴|language=ja|website=Yahoo News|location=Japan|publisher=Yahoo|date=19 February 2024|archive-date=19 February 2024|access-date=19 February 2024}}</ref>

The case was transferred to the [[Tokyo District Court]] in May and both Itō and the women were referred to prosecutors in July.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2 July 2024 |title=Japan footballer Junya Ito referred to prosecutors over sex assault claims|url=https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2024/07/26ec75844199-japan-footballer-ito-referred-to-prosecutors-over-sex-assault-claims.html|newspaper=Kyodo News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yomiuri.co.jp/national/20240702-OYT1T50152/|script-title=ja:性被害問題、伊東純也選手と女性２人の双方を書類送検…大阪地検が刑事処分を判断 |date=2 July 2024 |language=ja|website=Yomiuri}}</ref> On 9 August, prosecutors dropped both charges against Ito and Ito's countersuit on his accusers, citing lack of evidence.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2024/08/a14b0928028a-sex-assault-case-against-japanese-footballer-ito-dropped.html|title=Sex assault case against Japanese footballer Junya Ito dropped|newspaper=Kyodo News|date=9 August 2024}}</ref>

